## üìò Overview

The **Universal Transition Structure (UTS)** is the **central synthesis model** for the Codex.

It formulates a triadic relation between:

- **M√∂bius Collapse** \( e^{-C(x)} \) ‚Äî topological compression, complexity reduction.
- **Harmonic Resonance** \( H(x) \) ‚Äî frequency alignment, periodic stability.
- **Transition Layer** \( UTS(x) \) ‚Äî universal mapping of collapse and resonance.

The UTS equation defines their **equivalence**:

$$
e^{-C(x)} = UTS(x) = H(x)
$$

This structure is the formal convergence point of the **M√∂bius‚ÄìResonance Synthesis** guiding all Millennium Codex mappings.

---

## üßÆ Formal Structure

### Collapse Function

$$
C(x): \text{Topological Complexity ‚Üí Reduction Path}
$$

### Harmonic Function

$$
H(x): \text{Frequency Structure ‚Üí Stability Alignment}
$$

### Transition Equivalence

$$
e^{-C(x)} = H(x)
$$

- **Collapse** reduces topological complexity.
- **Harmonics** stabilize structural frequencies.
- **UTS** bridges both via an exponential collapse‚Äìresonance map.

